  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 60,
    "text": "The Temple support staff and Solomon's servants added up to 392."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 61,
    "text": "These are those who came from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Kerub, Addon, and Immer. They weren't able to prove their ancestry, whether they were true Israelites or not:"
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 62,
    "text": "The sons of Delaiah, Tobiah, and Nekoda, 642."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 63,
    "text": "Likewise with these priestly families: -The sons of Hobaiah, Hakkoz, and Barzillai, who had married a daughter of Barzillai the Gileadite and took that name."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 64,
    "text": "They looked high and low for their family records but couldn't find them. And so they were barred from priestly work as ritually unclean."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 65,
    "text": "The governor ruled that they could not eat from the holy food until a priest could determine their status by using the Urim and Thummim."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 66,
    "text": "The total count for the congregation was 42,360."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 67,
    "text": "That did not include the male and female slaves who numbered 7,337. There were also 245 male and female singers."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 68,
    "text": "And there were 736 horses, 245 mules,"
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 69,
    "text": "435 camels, and 6,720 donkeys."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 70,
    "text": "Some of the heads of families made voluntary offerings for the work. The governor made a gift to the treasury of 1,000 drachmas of gold (about nineteen pounds), 50 bowls, and 530 garments for the priests."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 71,
    "text": "Some of the heads of the families made gifts to the treasury for the work; it came to 20,000 drachmas of gold and 2,200 minas of silver (about one and a third tons)."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 72,
    "text": "Gifts from the rest of the people totaled 20,000 drachmas of gold (about 375 pounds), 2,000 minas of silver, and 67 garments for the priests."
  },
  {
    "book_id": "NEH",
    "book_name": "Nehemiah",
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 73,
    "text": "The priests, Levites, security guards, singers, and Temple support staff, along with some others, and the rest of the People of Israel, all found a place to live in their own towns."
  }
]